When adding bookmarks I'd like to save the content and ideally search it. How can I do this?

A lot of times I remember pieces of content but don't not the title of the article, making it hard to find something I'm looking for. Also some of the sites just disappear after some time.
stories.title: Ask HN: How to save bookmarks locally including searchable content?

stories.text: Trafalgar Equipment Ltd., for the past 25 years, is a Canadian-owned industrial trailer rental business in Hamilton. We have consistently provided affordable prices to our consumers throughout the years, as well as services such as trailer delivery and pickup throughout the GTA. We attempt to provide reasonable short and long-term lease choices with our competitive price. We can also bring a 48-foot or 53-foot trailer with barn style or roll-up doors to your location or keep it in our secure yard. All of our trailers are routinely serviced and cleaned to guarantee that no issues arise during your rental period. However, if you have any issues with your trailer, please contact us and we will assist you. Visit our website at https://trafalgarequipment.com/industrial-trailer-rentals/ and get a free quote!
